{"title": "Unsanitized user input in HTTP request (SSRF)", "summary": "  Applications should not connect to locations formed from user input. This rule checks for URLs containing user-supplied data. ", "description": "\n\nApplications should not connect to locations formed from user input.\nThis rule checks for URLs containing user-supplied data.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid using user input in HTTP URLs:\n\n```javascript\nconst response = axios.get(`https://${req.params.host}`)\n```\n\n\u2705 Use user input indirectly to form a URL:\n\n```javascript\nconst hosts = new Map([\n  [\"option1\", \"api1.com\"],\n  [\"option2\", \"api2.com\"]\n])\n\nconst host = hosts.get(req.params.host)\nconst response = axois.get(`https://${host}`)\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-918"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/javascript_lang_http_url_using_user_input"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}